name: dfs.namenode.decommission.max.concurrent.tracked.nodes
description:
The maximum number of decommission-in-progress or
    entering-maintenance datanodes nodes that will be tracked at one time by
    the namenode. Tracking these datanode consumes additional NN memory
    proportional to the number of blocks on the datnode. Having a conservative
    limit reduces the potential impact of decommissioning or maintenance of
    a large number of nodes at once.
      
    A value of 0 means no limit will be enforced.

name: fs.s3a.fast.upload.active.blocks
description:
Maximum Number of blocks a single output stream can have
    active (uploading, or queued to the central FileSystem
    instance's pool of queued operations.

    This stops a single stream overloading the shared thread pool.

name: mapreduce.reduce.shuffle.read.timeout
description:
Expert: The maximum amount of time (in milli seconds) reduce
  task waits for map output data to be available for reading after obtaining
  connection.

name: dfs.namenode.max-corrupt-file-blocks-returned
description:
The maximum number of corrupt file blocks listed by NameNode Web UI,
      JMX and other client request.

name: dfs.qjournal.start-segment.timeout.ms
description: Quorum timeout in milliseconds for starting a log segment.

name: dfs.ha.tail-edits.namenode-retries
description: Number of retries to use when contacting the namenode when tailing the log.

name: dfs.client.deadnode.detection.rpc.threads
description: The maximum number of threads to use for calling RPC call to recheck the liveness of dead node.

name: io.seqfile.compress.blocksize
description:
The minimum block size for compression in block compressed
          SequenceFiles.

name: dfs.datanode.ec.reconstruct.write.bandwidthPerSec
description:
Specifies the maximum amount of bandwidth that the EC reconstruction can utilize for writing.
      When the bandwidth value is zero, there is no limit.
